I"	<h1 id="welcome-fellow-traveller">Welcome, fellow traveller</h1>
<p>Thank you for visiting my small corner of the Internet world.</p>

<p>I am a student of philosophy, politics and economics at the London School of Economics.</p>

<p>I enjoy writing and thinking about economics, cities, and societal systems. I share my occasional pontificaitons about the world on <a href="https://matthewlhchiu.substack.com/">Substack</a>.</p>

<p>More generally, this website is a disparate collection of my thoughts, notes, and weakly-held opinions. I hope you find them interesting.</p>

<h2 id="my-work">My work</h2>
<p>I am currently working on research in <strong>AI governance</strong> and <strong>development economics</strong>. More generally, my interests are wide-ranging and include the economics of innovation, economic growth, development economics, labour allocation, and industrial organisation.</p>

<p>As a student of the social sciences and humanities, I have been blessed with the opportunity to think deeply about many problems. Amongst other topics, I have written (read: speculated) about:</p>
<ul>
  <li>the infamous <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sleeping_Beauty_problem">Sleeping Beauty problem</a> in formal epistemology (I’m a thirder!)</li>
  <li>why Karl Marx’s “dictatorship of the proletariat”, a transitionary state prior to communism, could be viable</li>
  <li>how sovereign wealth funds can curtail the resource curse</li>
  <li>the decline of Schumpeterian creative destruction for explaining low GDP growth</li>
</ul>

<p>Most recently, I have been thinking about how the systems that that shape us — the meritocratic ideal, the democratic spirit, the educational system, and the idol of prestige — came to be.</p>

<p>I previously worked in management consulting, venture capital and talent investing, and early-stage startups.</p>

